sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Creates a transfer order in SAP S/4HANA - RFC.

Inputs :

  • Connection Alias - Connection alias for SAP S/4HANA - RFC.
  • Warehouse number - It indicates an individual warehouse.
  • Movement Type - They are three digit code to identify type of movement in goods.
  • Commit work - It is a input provided the value X as per the requirement.
  • User Name - The name used to identify the user.
  • Only create TO - It is a input provided the value X as per the requirement.
  • Multi Item Transfer Orders - Complex object containing these fields:
    • Material Number
    • Plant
    • Storage Location
    • Batch
    • Stock Category
    • Special Stock
    • Special Stock Number
    • Storage Unit Type
    • Quantity requested
    • Alternative Unit of Measure
    • GR Date
    • SLED/BBD
    • Certificate Number
    • Confirm
    • Do not print
    • Printer
    • Goods recipient
    • Unloading Point
    • Source Storage Type
    • Source stor.section
    • Source Storage Bin
    • Source bin position
    • Source storage unit
    • Quant [ VLQNR ]
    • Dest. Storage Type
    • Dest.storage section
    • Dest.Storage Bin
    • Dest.bin position
    • Dest.storage unit
    • Quant [ NLQNR ]
    • Return storage type
    • Return storage area
    • Return storage bin
    • Quant [ RLQNR ]
    • Item (SD)
    • Kanban Indicator
    • Inspection GUID [ FROM_INSP_GUID ]
    • Inspection GUID [ TO_INSP_GUID ]
    • Inspection GUID [ RETURN_INSP_GUID ]
    • Table Row
    • Stock Segment
  • Transmission structure - Complex object containing these fields:
    • Client
    • Warehouse Number
    • Transfer Order Number
    • Movement type [ BWART ]
    • Movement type [ BWLVS ]
    • Transfer Priority
    • Shipment Type
    • Creation Date
    • Time created
    • User
    • Group
    • TR Number
    • PostingChange Number
    • Sales Document
    • Confirmation
    • Confirmation Date
    • Material Document
    • Material Doc. Year
    • Requirement Type
    • Requirement Number
    • Print code
    • Transfer Order Printed
    • Partially supplied
    • Ind: R/2 immediately
    • Ind: accumulated
    • Difference immediat.
    • Indicator: planned
    • Planned execution
    • Reservation
    • Additional Number
    • Requirement type
    • Control cycle number
    • Kanban item no.
    • Performance data
    • Actual time required in TO
    • Input rqmnt for act.data
    • Personnel Number
    • Plan Time WM
    • Plan Time External Sys.
    • Actual Time of WM Transfer Order
    • Time unit
    • Transfer Order HR Status
    • Start Date of the Transfer Order
    • Transfer Order End Date
    • Start time of the transfer order
    • Transfer Order End Time
    • Transfer Order Type
    • Lean WM
    • Door for Whse No.
    • Staging Area
    • Packaging in WM
    • Threshold deviation plan/actual time (%)
    • TO processing comment (code)
    • Special reference
    • SD document categ.
    • Queue
    • Separate confirmatn
    • Transfer order priority
    • Pick confirmed
    • Confirm HU
    • Number of line items
    • TRM
    • Delayed Update
    • Confirmation Transf.
    • TO for Multiple Deliv.
    • Number of items
    • Do not print
    • Actual data recorded
    • Partial allocation
    • Partial direct pickg
    • Only Items
    • Adopt Pick Quantity
    • Adopt putaway qty
  • Transmission structure for update task- Complex object containing these fields:
    • Client
    • Material Number
    • Plant
    • Batch Number
    • Special Stock
    • Storage Unit Type
    • Source Storage Type
    • Source stor.section
    • Source Storage Bin
    • Source target qty
    • Dest. Storage Type
    • Dest.storage section
    • Dest.Storage Bin
  • Additional Fields - Additional fields or values you want to add to the details. These fields are retrieved dynamically from SAP S/4HANA - RFC.

Outputs :

  • Transfer Order Details - Details of transfer order created in SAP S/4HANA - RFC.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in SAP S/4HANA - RFC, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages :

  • Encountered an error. Check log for more details.

 

To use this action, the corresponding SAP S/4HANA - RFC connection and credential must be created and associated with the SAP S/4HANA - RFC Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
